When @zara first approached Molly, Courtney, and I with the opportunity to partner with them to launch @livingzara I was excited about the creative opportunity but also of course apprehensive because I was unsure of their sustainability efforts.¬† Working with Zara was not a quick decision, and actually the first step was to speak with them directly about sustainability, and both their current actions and future intentions.¬† Progress is never overnight, especially for a large company with customers, employees, and investors.¬† I do believe Zara is and will continue to change, and this is why I agreed to work with them.¬† One small example is that just this week Inditex, Zara's parent company, made a donation to @mitpics for a multiyear research project on the topic of sustainability.¬† Also, after discussing with Zara I felt it was better to engage with a large company that was making efforts, and that I could perhaps continue to encourage in the long run, rather than avoid the conversation with them all together.¬† When I first started posting photos a few years ago it was never my intention to be a voice of public social commentary.¬† But the attention that has come my way has afforded me that opportunity, and it is not something I take lightly at all!¬† I love fashion but I am also a sister, daughter, friend, and many other things.¬† I care about social causes and our planet, and I am thankful that I have been given a platform that I can use to promote my my views and I truly do care about the environment and everything going on here on this planet and I truly do want to help better it.¬† I am 22 years old and I do not have all the answers.¬† I am learning on the job.¬† I will continue to do my best, as I have always done, and as I hope each and every one of you will do as well! Bodice Studio won the #woolmarkprize, which helped make it possible for @bodicebodice to create its AW18 collection. Designer Ruchika Sachdeva was inspired by her grandmother who used to upcycle saris to help reduce consumer waste in fashion. All of the garments were created from non toxic natural dyes and the waste from the dying process was composted. Just from wearing a few of the pieces from the collection I can tell how much thought went into every piece. The outfit I‚Äôm wearing is something I‚Äôve never seen before! I love the movement and adjustability to the clothes. All of the garment have adjustable fastenings to allow for natural changes to the human body. Any brand that puts this much thought into every detail of the creative process is definitely someone worth supporting!  The collection is available now @farfetch
